{"id": "duc04-testb-2:8#25", "contents": "Samaranch denied allegations that he had \"muzzled\" Hodler, explaining that he had instructed all executive board members to direct media inquiries to himself and the IOC's director general, Francois Carrad. He also ruled out the possibility of expelling Hodler from the IOC, stating, \"Never, never, is anyone thinking to expel Mr. Hodler.\" Samaranch expressed his respect and admiration for Hodler, acknowledging his contributions to the organization. The IOC also dismissed the possibility of stripping Salt Lake City of the 2002 Winter Games due to alleged rules violations during the bidding process."}
